<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Initial containing block for fixed positioned elements.</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#containing-block-details" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="The containing block is established by the viewport when an element uses fixed positioning." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #d1
            {
                position: relative;
                width: 360px;
                left: 100px;
                border: green 2px solid;
                height: 22px;
            }
            #d2
            {
                width: 300px;
                height: 25px;
            }
            #d3
            {
                position: fixed;
                top: 11px;
                left: 120px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div id="d1"></div>
        <div id="d2">
            <div id="d3">Filler Text Filler Text Filler Text Filler Text Filler Text</div>
        </div>
        <p>Test passes if "Filler Text" is contained within the green box and does not overlap the borders.</p>
    </body>
</html>